a.xlink:title: Definition of exchanges of cash and/or securities available in the processing of corporate actions.

The definition of the securities proceeds for a corporate action in generic terms; that is, before applying it to specific securities holding. An example would be the definition of a bonus rights issue where all the information will be given in general on a per share basis.

Provides information about the alternatives available to an account owner when participating to a corporate action event. This is defined at a general level without looking at the specificities of the securities balances.
An event determined by a corporation's board of directors, that changes the existing corporate capital structure or financial condition.
Time span defined by a start date and time, and an end date and time.
Ratio expressed as a quotient of quantities.
